Attributes.description: Principles of cellular and organismal physiology illustrated with examples from unicellular organisms, plants and animals, focusing on transport processes, water balance, nutrient acquisition and communication.
Attributes.prereq: Pre-reqs: Either (a) all of BIOL 112, BIOL 121 or (b) SCIE 001. (or (c) 8 transfer credits of 1st year BIOL and 6 credits of 1st year chemistry.)
